Annotation

Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
The patient shows hypoglycemia, low HbA1c, elevated creatinine, and proteinuria, suggesting possible chronic kidney disease with impaired glucose regulation. Urine findings (cloudy, brown, low specific gravity, protein, glucose, ketones) may indicate renal dysfunction and possible dehydration. No evidence of urinary infection. Metabolic acidosis is suggested by low CO₂ and elevated chloride. Clinical correlation and further nephrological and metabolic evaluation are recommended.
